# Babylon Pizza — Online Ordering System
# Cursor Rules

## Project Scope
This project is ONLY the online ordering system for Babylon Pizza.
- The marketing/landing page is built separately by another developer
- This codebase covers: menu browsing, cart, checkout, order confirmation, order tracking, and the restaurant admin panel
- Do NOT build or modify anything related to the public-facing homepage or brand site

## Stack
- Framework: Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- Database: Neon (PostgreSQL via @neondatabase/serverless)
- ORM: Drizzle ORM
- Auth: NextAuth.js (email/password + social)
- Payments: Vipps MobilePay (primary, Norway) + Stripe (fallback)
- State: Zustand (cart state)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + CSS variables for brand tokens
- Animations: Framer Motion

## Brand Design Tokens
Use these CSS variables throughout. Never hardcode colors.

```css
:root {
  --color-bg:        #0a0a0a;
  --color-surface:   #141414;
  --color-border:    #1f1f1f;
  --color-gold:      #f5a800;
  --color-gold-dim:  #c88a00;
  --color-text:      #f0f0f0;
  --color-muted:     #888888;
  --color-danger:    #e03c3c;
  --color-success:   #2ecc71;

  --font-display: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;
  --font-body:    'DM Sans', sans-serif;

  --radius-sm: 4px;
  --radius-md: 8px;
  --radius-lg: 16px;
}
```

Load from Google Fonts: Bebas Neue (display), DM Sans (body).

## UI & Component Rules

### Buttons
- Primary CTA: `bg-[var(--color-gold)] text-black font-bold uppercase tracking-widest hover:bg-[var(--color-gold-dim)] transition-colors`
- Secondary: `border border-[var(--color-gold)] text-[var(--color-gold)] bg-transparent hover:bg-[var(--color-gold)]/10`
- Danger: `bg-[var(--color-danger)] text-white`
- Disabled state must always be visually distinct

### Cards (menu items)
- Dark surface `bg-[var(--color-surface)]` with `border border-[var(--color-border)]`
- Image top, content bottom
- Gold price label
- Green "VELG" (select) button — matches easybooking style but in brand palette
- Hover: subtle gold border glow `hover:border-[var(--color-gold)]/50`

### Cart Sidebar
- Fixed right panel, always visible on desktop (≥1024px)
- Slide-in drawer on mobile
- Shows item list, quantity controls (−/+/delete), discount code input, total, and "Send inn ordre" CTA
- Step progress indicator at top (1 → 2 → 3) using gold active color

### Layout
- Ordering pages use a two-column layout: menu (left, ~75%) + cart (right, ~25%)
- Mobile: single column, cart becomes bottom drawer/sheet
- Nav bar: black background, gold logo + location name on left, phone number on right

